00:19:18.330 --> 00:19:20.760 align:middle line:10%
In every great religion,
and religious and spiritual

00:19:20.760 --> 00:19:23.200 align:middle line:10%
philosophy, there is
always this notion

00:19:23.200 --> 00:19:26.880 align:middle line:10%
of paradise, this idea
of some perfect place.

00:19:26.880 --> 00:19:29.010 align:middle line:10%
And the idea of
paradise is this idea

00:19:29.010 --> 00:19:31.770 align:middle line:10%
of some place
where we have been,

00:19:31.770 --> 00:19:34.330 align:middle line:10%
and we're a longing
to get back to.

00:19:34.330 --> 00:19:36.770 align:middle line:10%
Well, why would it be
this primal archetype?

00:19:36.770 --> 00:19:38.520 align:middle line:10%
Why would it be in
all the religions?

00:19:38.520 --> 00:19:40.620 align:middle line:10%
Why would it be in
all the philosophies,

00:19:40.620 --> 00:19:43.890 align:middle line:10%
the idea of the promised
land, the idea of heaven,

00:19:43.890 --> 00:19:45.470 align:middle line:10%
this place we go to?

00:19:45.470 --> 00:19:48.080 align:middle line:10%
And, of course, it became
in traditional Christianity,

00:19:48.080 --> 00:19:51.580 align:middle line:10%
this idea of a place
we go to after we die.

00:19:51.580 --> 00:19:54.320 align:middle line:10%
But we don't go there
after we die physically

00:19:54.320 --> 00:19:56.550 align:middle line:10%
from an esoteric
perspective, we go there

00:19:56.550 --> 00:19:58.710 align:middle line:10%
after we die to who we are.

00:19:58.710 --> 00:20:01.920 align:middle line:10%
So the things of this
world can bring us

00:20:01.920 --> 00:20:04.800 align:middle line:10%
sort of temporary sursis
from existential pain.

00:20:04.800 --> 00:20:06.780 align:middle line:10%
But the real
happiness that we want

00:20:06.780 --> 00:20:09.790 align:middle line:10%
is the soul's longing for
that condition of paradise.

00:20:09.790 --> 00:20:12.390 align:middle line:10%
And the ego says, well, it will
be paradise when I have this,

00:20:12.390 --> 00:20:14.480 align:middle line:10%
or it will be paradise
when I have that.

00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:18.660 align:middle line:10%
And, of course, the
sad game of that

00:20:18.660 --> 00:20:20.490 align:middle line:10%
is that you get that,
and somehow it's

00:20:20.490 --> 00:20:23.690 align:middle line:10%
never quite all the things
you thought it would be.

00:20:23.690 --> 00:20:26.230 align:middle line:10%
That's because what we
really long for is paradise.

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:29.710 align:middle line:10%
What we really long
for is the real world.

00:20:29.710 --> 00:20:32.340 align:middle line:10%
And the real world is that
which lies beyond this world

00:20:32.340 --> 00:20:33.959 align:middle line:10%
entirely.

00:20:33.959 --> 00:20:35.750 align:middle line:10%
As a matter of fact,
"A Course of Miracles"

00:20:35.750 --> 00:20:38.110 align:middle line:10%
says that the ascetic
who denies the world

00:20:38.110 --> 00:20:40.250 align:middle line:10%
is just making the flip
mistake of someone who

00:20:40.250 --> 00:20:42.790 align:middle line:10%
throws themselves into
the world too much.

00:20:42.790 --> 00:20:44.890 align:middle line:10%
Neither can find joy here.

00:20:44.890 --> 00:20:47.310 align:middle line:10%
The joy that we
all seek is found

00:20:47.310 --> 00:20:50.940 align:middle line:10%
when we appreciate
our presence here,

00:20:50.940 --> 00:20:53.870 align:middle line:10%
but we recognize
that the real world

00:20:53.870 --> 00:20:56.850 align:middle line:10%
lies beyond the
perceptual filter.

00:20:56.850 --> 00:20:59.250 align:middle line:10%
The perceptual filter
that is taught us

00:20:59.250 --> 00:21:02.080 align:middle line:10%
by the thought system
that dominates this world.

00:21:02.080 --> 00:21:03.970 align:middle line:10%
In "A Course of
Miracles," it says

00:21:03.970 --> 00:21:07.250 align:middle line:10%
that you did not
author yourself.

00:21:07.250 --> 00:21:09.380 align:middle line:10%
God authored you.

00:21:09.380 --> 00:21:12.440 align:middle line:10%
It's not something we
create, and to the extent

00:21:12.440 --> 00:21:17.420 align:middle line:10%
to which we think it is ours
to create to that extent,

00:21:17.420 --> 00:21:18.420 align:middle line:10%
we are off.

00:21:18.420 --> 00:21:23.720 align:middle line:10%
We have disconnected ourselves
with that which is our source.

00:21:23.720 --> 00:21:26.730 align:middle line:10%
And to the extent to which we
have disconnected ourselves

00:21:26.730 --> 00:21:28.710 align:middle line:10%
from that which is
our source, we're

00:21:28.710 --> 00:21:31.400 align:middle line:10%
not receiving the
energy which is

00:21:31.400 --> 00:21:33.930 align:middle line:10%
both the essence of who we are.

00:21:33.930 --> 00:21:38.450 align:middle line:10%
But also, you're not just a
particle, you're also a wave.

00:21:38.450 --> 00:21:40.660 align:middle line:10%
When you have an
authority problem,

00:21:40.660 --> 00:21:44.820 align:middle line:10%
it is always because you believe
you are the author of yourself

00:21:44.820 --> 00:21:48.410 align:middle line:10%
and project your
delusion onto others.

00:21:48.410 --> 00:21:50.190 align:middle line:10%
So that's the second mistake.

00:21:50.190 --> 00:21:52.460 align:middle line:10%
If I'm unclear
about who I really

00:21:52.460 --> 00:21:57.000 align:middle line:10%
am, not recognizing that I'm
an idea in the mind of God,

00:21:57.000 --> 00:22:01.620 align:middle line:10%
I will also be incorrect
in my assessment of you.

00:22:01.620 --> 00:22:06.070 align:middle line:10%
Because when I'm not in a very
clear fundamental understanding

00:22:06.070 --> 00:22:08.010 align:middle line:10%
of who I am and
where I came from,

00:22:08.010 --> 00:22:10.760 align:middle line:10%
not as something that is
up to me to decide, well,

00:22:10.760 --> 00:22:11.400 align:middle line:10%
who are you?

00:22:11.400 --> 00:22:12.810 align:middle line:10%
Decide who you want to be.

00:22:12.810 --> 00:22:13.970 align:middle line:10%
No, no, no.

00:22:13.970 --> 00:22:17.260 align:middle line:10%
When you realize you don't
decide who you want to be.

00:22:17.260 --> 00:22:20.620 align:middle line:10%
You realize who you already are.

00:22:20.620 --> 00:22:24.410 align:middle line:10%
If I'm disconnected from the
realization of who I am, then

00:22:24.410 --> 00:22:28.550 align:middle line:10%
by definition, I'm
not in my right mind.

00:22:28.550 --> 00:22:31.010 align:middle line:10%
And when I'm not
in my right mind,

00:22:31.010 --> 00:22:34.770 align:middle line:10%
I won't see you
as you truly are.

00:22:34.770 --> 00:22:36.920 align:middle line:10%
You then perceive
the situation as one

00:22:36.920 --> 00:22:39.920 align:middle line:10%
in which others are
literally fighting you

00:22:39.920 --> 00:22:42.080 align:middle line:10%
for your authorship.

00:22:42.080 --> 00:22:44.940 align:middle line:10%
So then I get into a
realm of consciousness

00:22:44.940 --> 00:22:48.000 align:middle line:10%
where I don't recognize
that you are one with me.

00:22:48.000 --> 00:22:50.880 align:middle line:10%
If I realized that
I am a child of God,

00:22:50.880 --> 00:22:52.870 align:middle line:10%
that I'm just an idea
in the mind of God,

00:22:52.870 --> 00:22:55.790 align:middle line:10%
then, and only then,
do I get to realize

00:22:55.790 --> 00:22:58.090 align:middle line:10%
that you are the same thing.

00:22:58.090 --> 00:23:01.980 align:middle line:10%
And on that realm, there is
no separation between us.

00:23:01.980 --> 00:23:07.150 align:middle line:10%
On that realm, there is
no competition between us.

00:23:07.150 --> 00:23:10.040 align:middle line:10%
If my energy is not coming
from love, compassion,

00:23:10.040 --> 00:23:13.110 align:middle line:10%
and forgiveness by whatever
name I give it, then

00:23:13.110 --> 00:23:15.400 align:middle line:10%
I am making a
world that will not

00:23:15.400 --> 00:23:18.110 align:middle line:10%
