process, but you come to--

00:26:06.840 --> 00:26:08.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It takes a little bit.

00:26:08.210 --> 00:26:09.585 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Of
course, it does,

00:26:09.585 --> 00:26:13.690 align:middle line:10%
and you come to realize you're
forgiving out of self-interest.

00:26:13.690 --> 00:26:17.100 align:middle line:10%
Because I can only have what
I'm willing to grant you.

00:26:17.100 --> 00:26:21.090 align:middle line:10%
So if once I realize that
my anger is not hurting you,

00:26:21.090 --> 00:26:23.450 align:middle line:10%
you're not even thinking
about this incident anymore,

00:26:23.450 --> 00:26:26.570 align:middle line:10%
but it's keeping the universe
from getting through to me,

00:26:26.570 --> 00:26:29.480 align:middle line:10%
because it can only come
through a conduit of love.

00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:32.570 align:middle line:84%
My anger and my unforgiveness
is not hurting you.

00:26:32.570 --> 00:26:34.130 align:middle line:90%
It's hurting me.

00:26:34.130 --> 00:26:38.000 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So essentially, that
universe is ready to provide.

00:26:38.000 --> 00:26:40.710 align:middle line:10%
It's ready to provide, and
it hits me, and it goes no.

00:26:40.710 --> 00:26:42.168 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: That's
exactly right.

