because the universe can.

00:33:59.340 --> 00:34:01.330 align:middle line:10%
The first sentence in
"A Course in Miracles"

00:34:01.330 --> 00:34:04.010 align:middle line:10%
is that there is no order
of difficulty in miracles.

00:34:04.010 --> 00:34:06.850 align:middle line:10%
If it's a small hole, a
big hole in the ocean,

00:34:06.850 --> 00:34:09.960 align:middle line:10%
doesn't matter the shape of the
hole or the size of the hole,

00:34:09.960 --> 00:34:12.310 align:middle line:10%
the universe has enough water.

00:34:12.310 --> 00:34:14.630 align:middle line:10%
And that is the law of
divine compensation,

00:34:14.630 --> 00:34:19.239 align:middle line:10%
that even if there is material
lack or material diminishment,

00:34:19.239 --> 00:34:23.219 align:middle line:10%
there is, in the realm
of spiritual substance,

00:34:23.219 --> 00:34:26.780 align:middle line:10%
a capacity to compensate for
the lack or the diminishment

00:34:26.780 --> 00:34:27.906 align:middle line:10%
on the material plane.

00:34:27.906 --> 00:34:29.489 align:middle line:10%
That's the law of
divine compensation.

