those types of vague wealth?

00:34:44.850 --> 00:34:47.460 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well,
wealth of love,

00:34:47.460 --> 00:34:49.210 align:middle line:10%
love cannot be diminished
in the universe.

00:34:49.210 --> 00:34:50.668 align:middle line:10%
The only way love
can be diminished

00:34:50.668 --> 00:34:52.449 align:middle line:10%
in the universe
is if we ourselves

00:34:52.449 --> 00:34:53.830 align:middle line:10%
refuse to generate it.

00:34:53.830 --> 00:34:56.150 align:middle line:10%
So in the universe,
the whole point

00:34:56.150 --> 00:34:59.950 align:middle line:10%
is that on the spiritual
plane, there is no lack.

00:34:59.950 --> 00:35:02.520 align:middle line:10%
It's only on the material plane
that lack and diminishment

00:35:02.520 --> 00:35:03.700 align:middle line:10%
can show up.

00:35:03.700 --> 00:35:07.010 align:middle line:10%
So the universe is
set up for healing.

00:35:07.010 --> 00:35:09.070 align:middle line:10%
There could be
psychological wounding.

00:35:09.070 --> 00:35:10.647 align:middle line:10%
There can be emotional wounding.

00:35:10.647 --> 00:35:11.230 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Right.

00:35:11.230 --> 00:35:12.979 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: And even
then, because there

00:35:12.979 --> 00:35:16.830 align:middle line:10%
is no spot where
love is not, even

00:35:16.830 --> 00:35:19.530 align:middle line:10%
when we are psychologically
damaged or emotionally damaged,

00:35:19.530 --> 00:35:20.860 align:middle line:10%
they say time heals.

00:35:20.860 --> 00:35:22.170 align:middle line:10%
Situations heal.

00:35:22.170 --> 00:35:23.450 align:middle line:10%
We can be healed.

00:35:23.450 --> 00:35:26.150 align:middle line:10%
So the universe always
has a healing mechanism.

00:35:26.150 --> 00:35:27.239 align:middle line:90%
That's the point.

00:35:27.239 --> 00:35:29.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then how do
you tap, I guess, into it?

00:35:29.280 --> 00:35:31.810 align:middle line:10%
Look about relationships, I
mean, so many relationships

00:35:31.810 --> 00:35:34.250 align:middle line:10%
that are devastated by finances.

00:35:34.250 --> 00:35:38.800 align:middle line:10%
Fighting about money, it really
takes apart a relationship.

00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:41.580 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: I think one of
the things that Americans need

00:35:41.580 --> 00:35:44.210 align:middle line:10%
to do is we need to put
our intimate relationships

00:35:44.210 --> 00:35:45.820 align:middle line:10%
in a sacred container.

00:35:45.820 --> 00:35:49.400 align:middle line:10%
I think we let-- It's like
if you have an intimate love,

00:35:49.400 --> 00:35:50.970 align:middle line:10%
and marriages
should be this way,

00:35:50.970 --> 00:35:53.680 align:middle line:10%
love affairs should be this
way, family should be this way,

00:35:53.680 --> 00:35:56.507 align:middle line:10%
you need to put it in
a psychic container.

00:35:56.507 --> 00:35:58.840 align:middle line:10%
And that's why families who
pray together stay together.

00:35:58.840 --> 00:35:59.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:35:59.770 --> 00:36:01.811 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: The Catholics
are right about that.

00:36:01.811 --> 00:36:04.320 align:middle line:84%
It's not just because there's
an injunction against divorce.

00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:08.010 align:middle line:84%
It's because you have to
decide what's important here,

00:36:08.010 --> 00:36:11.490 align:middle line:84%
and if you let things like
money-- money comes and goes.

00:36:11.490 --> 00:36:15.360 align:middle line:84%
And that's the whole idea of
for richer or for poorer, hello,

00:36:15.360 --> 00:36:17.199 align:middle line:84%
that our love will
not be based on this.

00:36:17.199 --> 00:36:18.990 align:middle line:84%
But too many Americans,
you have the TV on,

00:36:18.990 --> 00:36:20.480 align:middle line:90%
you have the salt of modernity.

00:36:20.480 --> 00:36:23.470 align:middle line:10%
That's why a Sabbath is
very important concept,

00:36:23.470 --> 00:36:26.655 align:middle line:10%
that one day of the week, we
will turn off the electronics,

00:36:26.655 --> 00:36:29.680 align:middle line:10%
and we will just
be with each other.

00:36:29.680 --> 00:36:31.600 align:middle line:10%
And if we do not
build, we do not

00:36:31.600 --> 00:36:36.640 align:middle line:10%
work at building this sacred
substance of our relationships

00:36:36.640 --> 00:36:39.120 align:middle line:10%
enough in order that
they are protected,

00:36:39.120 --> 00:36:41.490 align:middle line:10%
that's what spending
time together does.

00:36:41.490 --> 00:36:43.880 align:middle line:10%
Turning off the TV,
turning off the computers,

00:36:43.880 --> 00:36:45.700 align:middle line:10%
doing things together,
communicating

00:36:45.700 --> 00:36:48.302 align:middle line:10%
at a deep level,
parents, children.

00:36:48.302 --> 00:36:49.760 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Because in
the big picture,

00:36:49.760 --> 00:36:51.590 align:middle line:10%
it shouldn't matter what you--

00:36:51.590 --> 00:36:54.200 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well, I mean
it's a very stressful thing.

00:36:54.200 --> 00:36:56.440 align:middle line:10%
I mean, this is not
about denying that.

00:36:56.440 --> 00:36:59.980 align:middle line:10%
No, Susie, mommy and daddy can't
pay for your ballet classes

00:36:59.980 --> 00:37:00.680 align:middle line:10%
this year.

00:37:00.680 --> 00:37:03.860 align:middle line:10%
This is not like there's
no point minimizing it,

00:37:03.860 --> 00:37:06.600 align:middle line:10%
it's the point how
much mommy and daddy

00:37:06.600 --> 00:37:10.240 align:middle line:10%
are able to hold it that,
you know, Susie, guess what?

00:37:10.240 --> 00:37:13.420 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to do ballet
this year, but guess what?

00:37:13.420 --> 00:37:15.410 align:middle line:84%
We found this park
that we can all

00:37:15.410 --> 00:37:17.490 align:middle line:84%
go take free swing
dances this year.

00:37:17.490 --> 00:37:18.960 align:middle line:90%
Do you see what I'm saying?

00:37:18.960 --> 00:37:21.490 align:middle line:10%
It's what you-- how you can
emotionally and psychologically

00:37:21.490 --> 00:37:22.700 align:middle line:10%
compensate.

00:37:22.700 --> 00:37:26.440 align:middle line:10%
Because if the parents just
implode, then, of course,

00:37:26.440 --> 00:37:28.400 align:middle line:10%
the children will
just follow suit.

00:37:28.400 --> 00:37:30.441 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: And, well, then
look at the relationship,

00:37:30.441 --> 00:37:32.525 align:middle line:10%
then, between the
parents, because any time

00:37:32.525 --> 00:37:33.900 align:middle line:10%
that they spend
together is spent

00:37:33.900 --> 00:37:35.780 align:middle line:10%
on financial
conversations and things

00:37:35.780 --> 00:37:38.037 align:middle line:10%
they can't do our buy
because of finances.

00:37:38.037 --> 00:37:40.370 align:middle line:10%
It would take the relationship
in a completely different

00:37:40.370 --> 00:37:40.871 align:middle line:10%
direction.

00:37:40.871 --> 00:37:42.536 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: And
that goes back to what

00:37:42.536 --> 00:37:44.960 align:middle line:10%
we were talking about earlier
about the psychic crisis

00:37:44.960 --> 00:37:48.900 align:middle line:10%
that it is for men more than for
women when they can't produce,

00:37:48.900 --> 00:37:50.430 align:middle line:10%
they can't support
their families.

00:37:50.430 --> 00:37:53.400 align:middle line:10%
This is not just a
material crisis for a man

00:37:53.400 --> 00:37:54.630 align:middle line:10%
much more than for a woman.

00:37:54.630 --> 00:37:56.729 align:middle line:10%
It's an emotional and
psychological crisis.

00:37:56.729 --> 00:37:58.270 align:middle line:10%
And that's why I
think it's important

00:37:58.270 --> 00:38:00.375 align:middle line:10%
that women understand
this and do everything

00:38:00.375 --> 00:38:05.130 align:middle line:10%
that we can to make sure that
the man-- the last thing he

00:38:05.130 --> 00:38:07.720 align:middle line:10%
needs is the emasculation
of feeling like his family

00:38:07.720 --> 00:38:08.800 align:middle line:10%
doesn't respect him.

00:38:08.800 --> 00:38:09.435 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: That he can't provide.

00:38:09.435 --> 00:38:10.090 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Yeah.

00:38:10.090 --> 00:38:10.740 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:38:10.740 --> 00:38:11.420 align:middle line:10%
It's important.

00:38:11.420 --> 00:38:12.160 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: So there are
deep issues involved here.

00:38:12.160 --> 00:38:14.100 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Especially
with women making money

00:38:14.100 --> 00:38:17.670 align:middle line:10%
and being in the workforce,
and it not being a competition.

00:38:17.670 --> 00:38:18.740 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Right.

00:38:18.740 --> 00:38:20.198 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: And that's
something that's

00:38:20.198 --> 00:38:23.320 align:middle line:10%
very important is that if a
woman is working and bringing

00:38:23.320 --> 00:38:25.800 align:middle line:10%
in money, it shouldn't
demasculate a man.

00:38:25.800 --> 00:38:28.150 align:middle line:10%
But there's ways to
do it where you still

00:38:28.150 --> 00:38:31.480 align:middle line:10%
maintain the relationship
and be partners, and be

00:38:31.480 --> 00:38:34.360 align:middle line:10%
equals, and still
feel like you have

00:38:34.360 --> 00:38:37.460 align:middle line:10%
that wonderful-- a man
needs to feel in some way

00:38:37.460 --> 00:38:41.910 align:middle line:10%
that he is a protector
or in some way

00:38:41.910 --> 00:38:43.400 align:middle line:10%
the man in the relationship.

00:38:43.400 --> 00:38:44.050 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: I agree with that.

00:38:44.050 --> 00:38:46.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, I've
experienced that same thing,

00:38:46.030 --> 00:38:48.650 align:middle line:84%
and I have an amazing
relationship with my husband.

00:38:48.650 --> 00:38:53.000 align:middle line:10%
And he looks at that as I
don't rely on him to provide,

00:38:53.000 --> 00:38:57.050 align:middle line:10%
but I do not say you're
wrong for not doing

00:38:57.050 --> 00:38:59.260 align:middle line:10%
that so, therefore,
we have a totally

00:38:59.260 --> 00:39:01.830 align:middle line:10%
equal wonderful relationship
in terms of finances,

00:39:01.830 --> 00:39:03.660 align:middle line:10%
and it's not a problem.

00:39:03.660 --> 00:39:05.720 align:middle line:10%
And it's not a
competition, it's fun,

00:39:05.720 --> 00:39:07.470 align:middle line:10%
but it's also a
great conversation.

00:39:07.470 --> 00:39:11.410 align:middle line:10%
OK, so I'm reminded of
my mother-in-law who

00:39:11.410 --> 00:39:18.090 align:middle line:10%
is 75, lost her pension,
lost her savings

00:39:18.090 --> 00:39:20.810 align:middle line:10%
when a lot of things
change in terms

00:39:20.810 --> 00:39:22.930 align:middle line:10%
of the rules and
laws of finances.

00:39:22.930 --> 00:39:25.970 align:middle line:10%
She lost a lot of money there,
and she can't find a job now.

00:39:25.970 --> 00:39:28.800 align:middle line:10%
She's 75, "nobody
wants to hire me."

00:39:28.800 --> 00:39:31.060 align:middle line:10%
I get a lot of those
callers on my radio show.

00:39:31.060 --> 00:39:34.170 align:middle line:10%
What do I do if I am
older, and I'm not

00:39:34.170 --> 00:39:36.400 align:middle line:10%
hireable at this point in time?

00:39:36.400 --> 00:39:38.440 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well,
you know, I'm not

00:39:38.440 --> 00:39:42.890 align:middle line:10%
minimizing the problem
on a material plane,

00:39:42.890 --> 00:39:45.004 align:middle line:10%
but the universe is
infinitely malleable.

00:39:45.004 --> 00:39:47.420 align:middle line:10%
We don't believe in a God who
says, "I'd love to help you,

00:39:47.420 --> 00:39:49.150 align:middle line:10%
but you're over 75."

00:39:49.150 --> 00:39:51.620 align:middle line:10%
And you know, if the
whole universe is

00:39:51.620 --> 00:39:54.470 align:middle line:10%
run by a consciousness,
number one,

00:39:54.470 --> 00:39:57.470 align:middle line:10%
that we know we don't need
1,000 jobs, we need one.

00:39:57.470 --> 00:40:00.225 align:middle line:10%
And also, if the
entire society, it

00:40:00.225 --> 00:40:04.000 align:middle line:10%
used to be that parents came
in, lived with families more.

00:40:04.000 --> 00:40:06.100 align:middle line:10%
I mean, everything
relates to everything.

00:40:06.100 --> 00:40:09.100 align:middle line:10%
And in a society where old
people are so disposable,

00:40:09.100 --> 00:40:13.390 align:middle line:10%
and we sort of throw them
away, that's as big a problem.

00:40:13.390 --> 00:40:16.690 align:middle line:10%
So theoretically, when
everything works together,

00:40:16.690 --> 00:40:18.260 align:middle line:10%
the older person
doesn't have to fear

00:40:18.260 --> 00:40:21.510 align:middle line:10%
so much, because you take
care of your parents.

00:40:21.510 --> 00:40:23.790 align:middle line:10%
You take care of those who
years ago took care of you.

00:40:23.790 --> 00:40:24.810 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:40:24.810 --> 00:40:27.230 align:middle line:10%
In other countries it
is that way more so

00:40:27.230 --> 00:40:28.360 align:middle line:10%
than it is in this country.

00:40:28.360 --> 00:40:30.690 align:middle line:10%
We have a little bit
of that to get back to.

00:40:30.690 --> 00:40:32.746 align:middle line:10%
So there are some
