It's no different than
physical exercise.

00:43:20.970 --> 00:43:24.810 align:middle line:10%
Because whether you're talking
about your physical muscles

00:43:24.810 --> 00:43:28.220 align:middle line:10%
or your attitudinal muscles,
after a certain age if you're

00:43:28.220 --> 00:43:30.430 align:middle line:10%
not working at keeping
them up, their headed down.

00:43:30.430 --> 00:43:31.290 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: True.

00:43:31.290 --> 00:43:33.539 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: So you work
it, and it's like yoga, too.

00:43:33.539 --> 00:43:34.830 align:middle line:10%
Am I in the right position?

00:43:34.830 --> 00:43:35.510 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:43:35.510 --> 00:43:37.134 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: You're
working your body,

00:43:37.134 --> 00:43:39.600 align:middle line:10%
but it's your emotional body,
your psychological body,

00:43:39.600 --> 00:43:41.250 align:middle line:10%
your energetic body.

00:43:41.250 --> 00:43:42.500 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So what do you do?

00:43:42.500 --> 00:43:43.300 align:middle line:10%
What practices do you do?

00:43:43.300 --> 00:43:44.150 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON:
Well, I'm a student

00:43:44.150 --> 00:43:45.470 align:middle line:10%
of "A Course of Miracles."

00:43:45.470 --> 00:43:47.800 align:middle line:10%
I also do transcendental
meditation.

00:43:47.800 --> 00:43:51.220 align:middle line:10%
But the most important thing,
so I do pray and meditate

00:43:51.220 --> 00:43:55.360 align:middle line:10%
every day, but the most
important thing is to work it.

00:43:55.360 --> 00:43:59.720 align:middle line:10%
When I'm triggered, if
somebody does something

00:43:59.720 --> 00:44:02.300 align:middle line:10%
and I could be angry
about it, forgiveness.

00:44:02.300 --> 00:44:04.930 align:middle line:10%
I always say my life
works pretty well when

00:44:04.930 --> 00:44:06.290 align:middle line:10%
I practice what I preach.

00:44:06.290 --> 00:44:08.560 align:middle line:84%
And when I don't
practice what I preach,

00:44:08.560 --> 00:44:09.912 align:middle line:90%
these are impersonal laws.

00:44:09.912 --> 00:44:11.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You see the
difference between the two.

00:44:11.870 --> 00:44:12.661 align:middle line:90%
>>WILLIAMSON: Yeah.

00:44:12.661 --> 00:44:15.830 align:middle line:84%
Oh, yeah, it's a
whole different me.

00:44:15.830 --> 00:44:17.744 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What is your
relationship with money?

00:44:17.744 --> 00:44:19.410 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: My
relationship with money

00:44:19.410 --> 00:44:24.540 align:middle line:10%
is that I'm very blessed
and privileged that I've

00:44:24.540 --> 00:44:26.980 align:middle line:10%
had some successful books.

00:44:26.980 --> 00:44:32.150 align:middle line:10%
Where my weaknesses have been
has been, particularly earlier

00:44:32.150 --> 00:44:36.270 align:middle line:10%
in my career, not
managing it well.

00:44:36.270 --> 00:44:39.630 align:middle line:10%
When I first made money back
when my first book came out,

00:44:39.630 --> 00:44:43.700 align:middle line:10%
I made a mistake that I think
many people make when they just

00:44:43.700 --> 00:44:45.690 align:middle line:10%
make money quickly.

00:44:45.690 --> 00:44:47.820 align:middle line:10%
I thought it was
more than it was,

00:44:47.820 --> 00:44:49.750 align:middle line:10%
because it was
more than I'd seen.

00:44:49.750 --> 00:44:52.290 align:middle line:10%
And I remember
receiving in my mind

00:44:52.290 --> 00:44:55.780 align:middle line:10%
that I shouldn't do anything.

00:44:55.780 --> 00:44:58.540 align:middle line:10%
And I can see now why
that was my guidance.

00:44:58.540 --> 00:45:02.530 align:middle line:10%
Be in this new situation and
grow energetically into it.

00:45:02.530 --> 00:45:03.970 align:middle line:10%
I should have
learned about money.

00:45:03.970 --> 00:45:08.080 align:middle line:10%
I should have grown
said, OK, I have money

00:45:08.080 --> 00:45:12.500 align:middle line:10%
that I've never had
before, make me worthy.

00:45:12.500 --> 00:45:16.537 align:middle line:10%
Now become responsible, mature--

00:45:16.537 --> 00:45:17.370 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Accountable.

00:45:17.370 --> 00:45:20.610 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Accountable, sober
around it, emotionally sober.

00:45:20.610 --> 00:45:23.000 align:middle line:10%
And instead, I lived in
LA, got to buy a house.

00:45:23.000 --> 00:45:28.990 align:middle line:10%
And I can see where it took
me-- it was interesting

00:45:28.990 --> 00:45:31.860 align:middle line:10%
when that happened,
because I was spiritually

00:45:31.860 --> 00:45:35.830 align:middle line:10%
evolved enough to attract money,
but I wasn't psychologically

00:45:35.830 --> 00:45:40.221 align:middle line:10%
evolved enough to deal with
it well once it got here.

00:45:40.221 --> 00:45:41.970 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: That actually
makes perfect sense.

00:45:41.970 --> 00:45:44.730 align:middle line:10%
That's that marriage between
spiritual and physical

00:45:44.730 --> 00:45:46.105 align:middle line:10%
where you create
it in one level,

00:45:46.105 --> 00:45:47.688 align:middle line:10%
but you have to be
practical about it.

00:45:47.688 --> 00:45:48.370 align:middle line:90%
You have to be.

00:45:48.370 --> 00:45:49.995 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well,
you have to embody.

00:45:49.995 --> 00:45:52.400 align:middle line:84%
You have to become the
person who is the container.

00:45:52.400 --> 00:45:56.439 align:middle line:84%
And so I've had my ups and downs
like everybody else has had.

00:45:56.439 --> 00:45:58.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then how is
your relationship with it

00:45:58.480 --> 00:46:00.210 align:middle line:90%
now compared to then?

00:46:00.210 --> 00:46:02.450 align:middle line:10%
How did it change?

00:46:02.450 --> 00:46:04.180 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: My
ego mind sometimes

00:46:04.180 --> 00:46:08.100 align:middle line:10%
goes into, oh, I wish
that I'd been smarter back

00:46:08.100 --> 00:46:10.630 align:middle line:10%
in the 90s when my
first book came out.

00:46:10.630 --> 00:46:13.070 align:middle line:10%
Blah, blah, blah.

00:46:13.070 --> 00:46:15.110 align:middle line:10%
So it's one of those
when you say give up

00:46:15.110 --> 00:46:17.570 align:middle line:10%
your story so the universe
can write a new one,

00:46:17.570 --> 00:46:21.720 align:middle line:10%
I think, I like many, many
people look at the 90s,

00:46:21.720 --> 00:46:24.010 align:middle line:10%
and go, oh, my God, if only
I'd saved my money then.

00:46:24.010 --> 00:46:24.730 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Oh, yeah.

00:46:24.730 --> 00:46:26.650 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:46:26.650 --> 00:46:29.159 align:middle line:10%
Absolutely, well, I
mean, you could basically

00:46:29.159 --> 00:46:31.200 align:middle line:10%
read any page in your book
and just give yourself

00:46:31.200 --> 00:46:31.820 align:middle line:10%
a huge lesson.

00:46:31.820 --> 00:46:32.820 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Thank you.

00:46:32.820 --> 00:46:34.564 align:middle line:10%
You teach what
you need to learn.

00:46:34.564 --> 00:46:35.230 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Exactly.

00:46:35.230 --> 00:46:37.896 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: So the book is the
sharing of what I have learned.

00:46:37.896 --> 00:46:40.560 align:middle line:10%
And in that book I talk about,
as I talk about in all my work,

00:46:40.560 --> 00:46:42.640 align:middle line:10%
I've learned, as I
think most people have,

00:46:42.640 --> 00:46:44.515 align:middle line:10%
as much from my failures
as my successes.

00:46:44.515 --> 00:46:45.890 align:middle line:10%
As much from where
I've gotten it

00:46:45.890 --> 00:46:47.290 align:middle line:10%
wrong as where I've
gotten it right.

00:46:47.290 --> 00:46:49.373 align:middle line:10%
And sometimes something
you learn through failure,

00:46:49.373 --> 00:46:52.130 align:middle line:10%
you learn the hard way
is almost a lesson more

00:46:52.130 --> 00:46:53.210 align:middle line:10%
powerfully learned.

00:46:53.210 --> 00:46:54.580 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: That's why it's
good to write about it,

00:46:54.580 --> 00:46:56.600 align:middle line:10%
because then you get to share
your lessons with other people.

00:46:56.600 --> 00:46:57.060 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Yeah, hopefully.

00:46:57.060 --> 00:46:58.150 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: There's
another quote that I

00:46:58.150 --> 00:46:59.525 align:middle line:10%
think is really
powerful when you

00:46:59.525 --> 00:47:02.980 align:middle line:10%
talk about, "The universe
is the handwriting of God,

00:47:02.980 --> 00:47:05.710 align:middle line:10%
and is both self-organizing
and self-correcting,"

00:47:05.710 --> 00:47:07.860 align:middle line:10%
which we've been
talking a lot about.

00:47:07.860 --> 00:47:09.590 align:middle line:10%
"Where there is
lack, the universe

00:47:09.590 --> 00:47:12.870 align:middle line:10%
is already planning to remove
it from your circumstances."

00:47:12.870 --> 00:47:14.600 align:middle line:10%
Where there is
lack, the universe

00:47:14.600 --> 00:47:18.600 align:middle line:10%
is willing and ready to remove
it from your circumstances.

00:47:18.600 --> 00:47:20.720 align:middle line:10%
If we could just have
that in our minds,

00:47:20.720 --> 00:47:23.030 align:middle line:10%
if we could really
believe that, that's

00:47:23.030 --> 00:47:25.270 align:middle line:10%
what the entire law of
divine compensation is?

00:47:25.270 --> 00:47:26.770 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: "A
Course of Miracles"

00:47:26.770 --> 00:47:29.050 align:middle line:10%
says that whenever
there is a problem,

00:47:29.050 --> 00:47:32.730 align:middle line:10%
God creates the solution at
the moment the problem occurs.

00:47:32.730 --> 00:47:34.570 align:middle line:10%
The Native American
Indians used to say

00:47:34.570 --> 00:47:36.970 align:middle line:10%
that if there is a
poison in the forest,

00:47:36.970 --> 00:47:39.550 align:middle line:10%
the antidote to the poison is
within a certain number of feet

00:47:39.550 --> 00:47:40.540 align:middle line:10%
away.

00:47:40.540 --> 00:47:43.700 align:middle line:10%
And so when you live from
a spiritual perspective,

00:47:43.700 --> 00:47:47.910 align:middle line:10%
you know if there's a problem,
the answer is probably closer

00:47:47.910 --> 00:47:49.050 align:middle line:10%
than I think.

00:47:49.050 --> 00:47:52.000 align:middle line:10%
One of the areas where
I've seen this in my life,

00:47:52.000 --> 00:47:55.690 align:middle line:10%
where I can see all
the times when I just--

00:47:55.690 --> 00:47:57.910 align:middle line:10%
do you ever realize
you made a mistake,

00:47:57.910 --> 00:47:59.782 align:middle line:10%
you didn't take advantage
of an opportunity,

00:47:59.782 --> 00:48:02.400 align:middle line:10%
you went the wrong way, and
you look back in retrospect

00:48:02.400 --> 00:48:04.719 align:middle line:10%
and you think,
everything I needed

00:48:04.719 --> 00:48:05.760 align:middle line:10%
was right in front of me.

00:48:05.760 --> 00:48:06.450 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Oh, yes.

00:48:06.450 --> 00:48:08.116 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Everybody
I needed to talk

00:48:08.116 --> 00:48:09.534 align:middle line:10%
to was right in front of me.

00:48:09.534 --> 00:48:11.950 align:middle line:10%
You know, there's a man named
Mike Dugan who wrote a play.

00:48:11.950 --> 00:48:15.280 align:middle line:10%
And there's a line in the
play, "I laughed at the people

00:48:15.280 --> 00:48:16.780 align:middle line:10%
I should have listened to.

00:48:16.780 --> 00:48:19.741 align:middle line:10%
And I listened to the people
I should have laughed at."

00:48:19.741 --> 00:48:21.740 align:middle line:10%
And I think this is true
with money and business

00:48:21.740 --> 00:48:23.004 align:middle line:10%
as much as anything.

00:48:23.004 --> 00:48:23.920 align:middle line:10%
You're in front of me.

00:48:23.920 --> 00:48:26.580 align:middle line:10%
You're my friend, but I'm
assuming you don't know.

00:48:26.580 --> 00:48:29.716 align:middle line:10%
I'm going to go get some fancy
person who I think might know.

00:48:29.716 --> 00:48:31.090 align:middle line:10%
And you look back
and you realize

00:48:31.090 --> 00:48:33.670 align:middle line:10%
the universe had put
right in front of me

00:48:33.670 --> 00:48:36.180 align:middle line:10%
the person who had the
insight that I needed.

00:48:36.180 --> 00:48:39.490 align:middle line:84%
But when you don't realize it's
a self-organizing universe,

00:48:39.490 --> 00:48:41.360 align:middle line:84%
you think it must
be somewhere else.

00:48:41.360 --> 00:48:43.300 align:middle line:90%
I have to go find a job.

00:48:43.300 --> 00:48:46.370 align:middle line:10%
That's like another issue
there that I talk about

00:48:46.370 --> 00:48:49.340 align:middle line:10%
in the book is the difference
between a job and a calling.

00:48:49.340 --> 00:48:52.460 align:middle line:10%
People are out looking for
jobs, like it's out there

00:48:52.460 --> 00:48:53.705 align:middle line:10%
and I've got to find it.

00:48:53.705 --> 00:48:56.220 align:middle line:10%
But with a career
and a calling, you

00:48:56.220 --> 00:48:59.780 align:middle line:10%
realize there's something
that organically unfolds

00:48:59.780 --> 00:49:01.750 align:middle line:10%
from the field of
your own being.

00:49:01.750 --> 00:49:04.200 align:middle line:90%
You give birth to it.

00:49:04.200 --> 00:49:07.280 align:middle line:10%
There's that story, and most
of us have experienced this,

00:49:07.280 --> 00:49:10.840 align:middle line:10%
we've been one character
in the scenario or another.

00:49:10.840 --> 00:49:13.260 align:middle line:10%
Let's say there's a
man named William,

00:49:13.260 --> 00:49:16.120 align:middle line:10%
and William has a business idea.

00:49:16.120 --> 00:49:19.240 align:middle line:10%
And he feels absolutely
sure if he could only

00:49:19.240 --> 00:49:23.000 align:middle line:10%
talk to John Kerrigan.

00:49:23.000 --> 00:49:25.420 align:middle line:10%
I know John Kerrigan
would like my idea,

00:49:25.420 --> 00:49:27.500 align:middle line:10%
and John Kerrigan
is a huge investor.

00:49:27.500 --> 00:49:30.050 align:middle line:10%
I just know if I could
talk to John Kerrigan.

00:49:30.050 --> 00:49:32.259 align:middle line:10%
So he's going to a
party, and you probably

00:49:32.259 --> 00:49:33.550 align:middle line:10%
know where I'm going with this.

00:49:33.550 --> 00:49:36.080 align:middle line:10%
So William is going to a
party, and he has heard a rumor

00:49:36.080 --> 00:49:37.980 align:middle line:10%
that John Kerrigan
is going to be there.

00:49:37.980 --> 00:49:40.050 align:middle line:10%
So he's talking to people,
but he's really not

00:49:40.050 --> 00:49:40.740 align:middle line:10%
even talking to them.

00:49:40.740 --> 00:49:42.990 align:middle line:10%
He's looking past them to
see if maybe John Kerrigan--

00:49:42.990 --> 00:49:45.050 align:middle line:10%
you know how someone's
really looking past you

00:49:45.050 --> 00:49:46.840 align:middle line:10%
for somebody more interesting.

00:49:46.840 --> 00:49:49.850 align:middle line:84%
So William is talking to this
nice little old lady, right?

00:49:49.850 --> 00:49:53.237 align:middle line:10%
And John Kerrigan's
mind has, who is she

00:49:53.237 --> 00:49:55.476 align:middle line:10%
and what can she do for me?

00:49:55.476 --> 00:49:57.850 align:middle line:10%
And she's saying, well, tell
me about yourself young man.

00:49:57.850 --> 00:50:00.690 align:middle line:10%
Oh, I'm just here
ma'am, like he's

00:50:00.690 --> 00:50:02.040 align:middle line:10%
treating her like she's nothing.

00:50:02.040 --> 00:50:03.748 align:middle line:10%
Well, you know where
this story is going.

00:50:03.748 --> 00:50:06.070 align:middle line:10%
Later in the evening,
somebody says to William,

00:50:06.070 --> 00:50:08.590 align:middle line:10%
I saw you talking to
John Kerringan's mother.

00:50:08.590 --> 00:50:10.450 align:middle line:10%
Was she a nice woman?

00:50:10.450 --> 00:50:12.620 align:middle line:10%
And this woman had
tried to talk to him

00:50:12.620 --> 00:50:14.930 align:middle line:10%
and engage him in conversation.

00:50:14.930 --> 00:50:18.440 align:middle line:10%
So the universe
had brought to him

00:50:18.440 --> 00:50:22.990 align:middle line:10%
the best conduit by which
to get to John Kerrigan.

00:50:22.990 --> 00:50:25.376 align:middle line:10%
But number one, he didn't
realize the universe

00:50:25.376 --> 00:50:26.750 align:middle line:10%
is self-organizing,
so you should

00:50:26.750 --> 00:50:28.170 align:middle line:10%
be alert to
whatever's happening.

00:50:28.170 --> 00:50:31.240 align:middle line:10%
And number two, his heart
wasn't open to the human being

00:50:31.240 --> 00:50:32.530 align:middle line:10%
who is in front of him.

00:50:32.530 --> 00:50:35.040 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So the miracle
just, it went away,

00:50:35.040 --> 00:50:36.320 align:middle line:10%
and it wasn't in here.

00:50:36.320 --> 00:50:37.570 align:middle line:10%
It wasn't inside here.

00:50:37.570 --> 00:50:39.480 align:middle line:10%
It was out there and
reaching, and planning,

00:50:39.480 --> 00:50:40.430 align:middle line:10%
and going into action.

00:50:40.430 --> 00:50:43.005 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: As opposed to
knowing the universe is on it.

00:50:43.005 --> 00:50:46.190 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Well, I
do know where you

00:50:46.190 --> 00:50:48.660 align:middle line:10%
can get into that trap
of wanting to go out

00:50:48.660 --> 00:50:51.490 align:middle line:10%
after the goal, and you set it
into motion and all that stuff,

00:50:51.490 --> 00:50:54.460 align:middle line:10%
and then you realize
once you just give up--

00:50:54.460 --> 00:50:55.500 align:middle line:10%
and it's not giving up.

00:50:55.500 --> 00:50:57.902 align:middle line:10%
You use a specific word in
the book-- surrendering.

00:50:57.902 --> 00:51:00.110 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: You know the
"Course of Miracles" says,

00:51:00.110 --> 00:51:04.960 align:middle line:10%
liberation is not bursting
out but a gentle melting in.

00:51:04.960 --> 00:51:07.495 align:middle line:10%
You know when the
embryo becomes the baby,

00:51:07.495 --> 00:51:12.610 align:middle line:10%
the acorn becomes the oak tree,
the bud becomes the blossom,

00:51:12.610 --> 00:51:14.910 align:middle line:10%
you and I are
similarly programmed

00:51:14.910 --> 00:51:17.350 align:middle line:10%
to become the highest
best version of ourselves.

00:51:17.350 --> 00:51:20.240 align:middle line:10%
The universe is invested
in our self-actualization.

00:51:20.240 --> 00:51:23.866 align:middle line:84%
And the perfect career and
abundance is just part of that.

00:51:23.866 --> 00:51:26.240 align:middle line:84%
Now the difference between
us, and the embryo, the acorn,

00:51:26.240 --> 00:51:30.567 align:middle line:84%
and the bud is
that we can say no.

00:51:30.567 --> 00:51:31.900 align:middle line:10%
We can say, no, I don't want to.

00:51:31.900 --> 00:51:33.100 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Those active
minds of ours.

00:51:33.100 --> 00:51:34.280 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: They can't.

00:51:34.280 --> 00:51:34.860 align:middle line:10%
Pardon?

00:51:34.860 --> 00:51:35.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's right.

00:51:35.560 --> 00:51:35.960 align:middle line:90%
They can't.

00:51:35.960 --> 00:51:37.001 align:middle line:90%
>>WILLIAMSON: They can't.

00:51:37.001 --> 00:51:39.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: They cannot say no to
the self-organizing universe.

00:51:39.540 --> 00:51:41.165 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Right,
and you and I can.

00:51:41.165 --> 00:51:42.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And we can and we do.

00:51:42.390 --> 00:51:44.430 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: And not
only is it that God's plan

00:51:44.430 --> 00:51:47.560 align:middle line:84%
of the universe's plan works,
it's that ours doesn't.

00:51:47.560 --> 00:51:50.450 align:middle line:84%
So like that story of
William, he actually

00:51:50.450 --> 00:51:51.730 align:middle line:90%
interfered with the plan.

00:51:51.730 --> 00:51:54.021 align:middle line:10%
The plan was bringing everything
to him that he needed,

00:51:54.021 --> 00:51:57.330 align:middle line:10%
but he interfered by
having his own plan.

00:51:57.330 --> 00:51:59.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Self-limiting
thoughts, belief

00:51:59.040 --> 00:52:01.390 align:middle line:84%
that you can't do it,
that there's scarcity.

00:52:01.390 --> 00:52:03.280 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: That other
people don't matter.

00:52:03.280 --> 00:52:03.835 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or that--

00:52:03.835 --> 00:52:05.460 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: That
love and forgiveness

00:52:05.460 --> 00:52:07.250 align:middle line:90%
has nothing to do with this.

00:52:07.250 --> 00:52:08.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or that
the wrong person is

00:52:08.920 --> 00:52:13.410 align:middle line:84%
going to mess me over, and screw
me over, and all that, yes.

00:52:13.410 --> 00:52:16.130 align:middle line:84%
Those fear, like those
limiting thoughts.

00:52:16.130 --> 00:52:17.920 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: And
savvy, yes, wise, yes.

00:52:17.920 --> 00:52:20.240 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So what
is a good practice

00:52:20.240 --> 00:52:22.684 align:middle line:10%
when those thoughts come up?

00:52:22.684 --> 00:52:24.100 align:middle line:10%
If you're watching
this interview,

00:52:24.100 --> 00:52:25.558 align:middle line:10%
and you're getting
this, and you're

00:52:25.558 --> 00:52:28.600 align:middle line:10%
right here with us, what happens
when you come up against that,

00:52:28.600 --> 00:52:30.300 align:middle line:10%
OK, here's one of the
limiting thoughts,

00:52:30.300 --> 00:52:31.389 align:middle line:10%
what do I do with this?

00:52:31.389 --> 00:52:33.680 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well, if you've
meditated in the morning,

00:52:33.680 --> 00:52:35.200 align:middle line:10%
it won't come up so much.

00:52:35.200 --> 00:52:35.700 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: OK.

00:52:35.700 --> 00:52:36.242 align:middle line:10%
So good step.

00:52:36.242 --> 00:52:37.699 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Every
great religious

00:52:37.699 --> 00:52:39.490 align:middle line:10%
and spiritual tradition
that I've ever

00:52:39.490 --> 00:52:42.930 align:middle line:10%
read about emphasizes the
importance of the morning.

00:52:42.930 --> 00:52:45.200 align:middle line:10%
We wake up in the
morning, we take a shower.

00:52:45.200 --> 00:52:47.462 align:middle line:10%
You don't want yesterday's
dirt with you on your body

00:52:47.462 --> 00:52:48.420 align:middle line:10%
as you go into the day.

00:52:48.420 --> 00:52:48.950 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Right.

00:52:48.950 --> 00:52:50.575 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: But if
we don't meditate,

00:52:50.575 --> 00:52:53.050 align:middle line:10%
we're taking yesterday's
stress into the day.

00:52:53.050 --> 00:52:57.090 align:middle line:10%
So why would you be so careful
to wash your body but not

00:52:57.090 --> 00:52:59.180 align:middle line:10%
your mind and your
consciousness?

00:52:59.180 --> 00:53:00.640 align:middle line:10%
And that's why we
want to meditate.

00:53:00.640 --> 00:53:02.723 align:middle line:10%
Meditating in the morning,
praying in the morning,

00:53:02.723 --> 00:53:05.160 align:middle line:10%
centering ourselves
in right relationship

00:53:05.160 --> 00:53:07.220 align:middle line:10%
to the universe,
or the chances--

00:53:07.220 --> 00:53:08.720 align:middle line:10%
and then you know
what Americans do,

00:53:08.720 --> 00:53:11.310 align:middle line:10%
then we turn on the
TV, or the computer.

00:53:11.310 --> 00:53:13.890 align:middle line:10%
So not only are you
carrying your own stress,

00:53:13.890 --> 00:53:16.470 align:middle line:10%
you're carrying the stress
of everybody in Syria,

00:53:16.470 --> 00:53:19.960 align:middle line:10%
and the economy, and Somalia
and every place else.

00:53:19.960 --> 00:53:22.880 align:middle line:10%
So the idea of prayer and
meditation in the morning

00:53:22.880 --> 00:53:25.940 align:middle line:10%
is so that there will not
be as many frantic moments

00:53:25.940 --> 00:53:28.220 align:middle line:10%
where we would be vulnerable
to our own reactiveness

00:53:28.220 --> 00:53:30.520 align:middle line:10%
and our own impulsivity.

00:53:30.520 --> 00:53:35.210 align:middle line:10%
And if we are feeling ourselves,
I'm going insane right now.

00:53:35.210 --> 00:53:36.960 align:middle line:10%
I'm not being my truest self.

00:53:36.960 --> 00:53:40.140 align:middle line:10%
We have a practice by which to
say dear God, please help me.

00:53:40.140 --> 00:53:42.736 align:middle line:10%
I need help.

00:53:42.736 --> 00:53:44.360 align:middle line:10%
I know I shouldn't
be feeling this way,

00:53:44.360 --> 00:53:46.590 align:middle line:10%
but I really am, and
please protect me.

00:53:46.590 --> 00:53:48.470 align:middle line:10%
Otherwise, I might
push that send button,

00:53:48.470 --> 00:53:52.900 align:middle line:10%
I might send a text I'll regret
for of the rest of my life.

00:53:52.900 --> 00:53:54.620 align:middle line:10%
I might send an
email that will not

00:53:54.620 --> 00:53:56.710 align:middle line:10%
be a good email to
have in writing.

00:53:56.710 --> 00:53:58.099 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Just be aware of it.

00:53:58.099 --> 00:53:59.640 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: But
it's real difficult

00:53:59.640 --> 00:54:01.840 align:middle line:84%
if you haven't centered
yourself in spiritual practice

00:54:01.840 --> 00:54:02.300 align:middle line:90%
in the morning.

00:54:02.300 --> 00:54:03.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:54:03.220 --> 00:54:04.360 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:54:04.360 --> 00:54:06.560 align:middle line:10%
Marianne has a great
clip about the book.

00:54:06.560 --> 00:54:08.940 align:middle line:10%
She's actually reading
some of the great quotes

00:54:08.940 --> 00:54:11.990 align:middle line:10%
because there's so
many gems in this book.

00:54:11.990 --> 00:54:13.729 align:middle line:10%
Take a look at this.

00:54:13.729 --> 00:54:15.520 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Hi, I am
Marianne Williamson,

00:54:15.520 --> 00:54:16.570 align:middle line:10%
and I have a new book.

00:54:16.570 --> 00:54:19.230 align:middle line:10%
And it's called "The Law
of Divine Compensation."

00:54:19.230 --> 00:54:22.250 align:middle line:10%
In this book I take spiritual
principles and miracle minded

00:54:22.250 --> 00:54:24.550 align:middle line:10%
thinking, and I apply
them very specifically

00:54:24.550 --> 00:54:27.990 align:middle line:10%
to issues about work,
and money, and career.

00:54:27.990 --> 00:54:30.220 align:middle line:10%
Here's a little
bit from the book.

00:54:30.220 --> 00:54:31.900 align:middle line:10%
"When we think of
ourselves as channels

00:54:31.900 --> 00:54:34.640 align:middle line:10%
for the infinite creative
energy of the universe,

00:54:34.640 --> 00:54:38.070 align:middle line:10%
we think higher thoughts
than how will I get a job.

00:54:38.070 --> 00:54:39.810 align:middle line:10%
We're lifted to a
realm of consciousness

00:54:39.810 --> 00:54:42.460 align:middle line:10%
where questions like,
how can I best serve

00:54:42.460 --> 00:54:46.750 align:middle line:10%
the world take precedence over
what can I get out of this?

00:54:46.750 --> 00:54:49.700 align:middle line:10%
Within that realm, we
naturally do get a job.

00:54:49.700 --> 00:54:52.630 align:middle line:10%
We naturally do create
money, and we naturally

00:54:52.630 --> 00:54:55.540 align:middle line:10%
do produce an outer
prosperity that

00:54:55.540 --> 00:54:58.320 align:middle line:10%
reflects the prosperity
in our hearts.

00:54:58.320 --> 00:55:00.790 align:middle line:10%
This doesn't mean we don't
have to do the footwork,

00:55:00.790 --> 00:55:04.190 align:middle line:10%
but our feet become guided
by a wisdom we might not

00:55:04.190 --> 00:55:06.610 align:middle line:10%
have even known we had."

00:55:06.610 --> 00:55:08.590 align:middle line:10%
The idea I'm dealing
with here is the idea

00:55:08.590 --> 00:55:11.370 align:middle line:10%
that the universe is
both self-organizing and

00:55:11.370 --> 00:55:12.590 align:middle line:10%
self-correcting.

00:55:12.590 --> 00:55:14.030 align:middle line:10%
We are meant to prosper.

00:55:14.030 --> 00:55:16.570 align:middle line:10%
We are meant to be
lifted to the highest

00:55:16.570 --> 00:55:20.440 align:middle line:10%
level of creative possibility
in every area of our lives.

00:55:20.440 --> 00:55:22.120 align:middle line:10%
And "The Law of
Divine Compensation"

00:55:22.120 --> 00:55:24.480 align:middle line:10%
refers to the idea
that even when

00:55:24.480 --> 00:55:28.270 align:middle line:10%
we experience diminishment
within the material plane,

00:55:28.270 --> 00:55:31.030 align:middle line:10%
within the level of
spiritual substance,

00:55:31.030 --> 00:55:33.570 align:middle line:10%
there is more than enough
capacity for the universe

00:55:33.570 --> 00:55:35.940 align:middle line:10%
to compensate for any lack.

00:55:35.940 --> 00:55:38.880 align:middle line:10%
If those ideas seem
interesting to you,

00:55:38.880 --> 00:55:40.486 align:middle line:10%
I hope that you will
pick up the book.

00:55:40.486 --> 00:55:41.860 align:middle line:10%
And I hope that
you will not only

00:55:41.860 --> 00:55:43.800 align:middle line:10%
read it, but apply
the principles

00:55:43.800 --> 00:55:46.830 align:middle line:10%
and have all of the miracles
that I'm sure you desire.

00:55:46.830 --> 00:55:48.000 align:middle line:10%
We all do.

00:55:48.000 --> 00:55:48.500 align:middle line:10%
Thanks.

00:55:48.500 --> 00:55:55.671 align:middle line:90%


00:55:55.671 --> 00:55:57.670 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: I remember your
book, "A Return to Love"

00:55:57.670 --> 00:56:00.419 align:middle line:10%
and you basically rewrote
"A Course of Miracles"

00:56:00.419 --> 00:56:01.710 align:middle line:10%
so that we could understand it.

00:56:01.710 --> 00:56:03.690 align:middle line:10%
How long have you been studying
"A Course of Miracles?"

00:56:03.690 --> 00:56:05.565 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Well, yes,
"The Return to Love"

00:56:05.565 --> 00:56:06.979 align:middle line:10%
is like the cliff notes version.

00:56:06.979 --> 00:56:08.770 align:middle line:10%
I've been studying the
"Course of Miracles"

00:56:08.770 --> 00:56:11.910 align:middle line:10%
since 1970s, mid-70s
somewhere, like maybe

00:56:11.910 --> 00:56:15.720 align:middle line:10%
'77, something like that.

00:56:15.720 --> 00:56:19.210 align:middle line:10%
And I started lecturing
about it in 1983.

00:56:19.210 --> 00:56:20.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Just give
a brief description

00:56:20.900 --> 00:56:22.450 align:middle line:84%
of what "A Course
of Miracles" is.

00:56:22.450 --> 00:56:24.241 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: The course
has been described

00:56:24.241 --> 00:56:27.620 align:middle line:10%
as a self-study program of
spiritual psychotherapy.

00:56:27.620 --> 00:56:31.330 align:middle line:10%
It is a training in
relinquishing a thought system

00:56:31.330 --> 00:56:33.750 align:middle line:10%
based on fear, and
accepting, instead,

00:56:33.750 --> 00:56:36.020 align:middle line:10%
a thought system based on love.

00:56:36.020 --> 00:56:38.700 align:middle line:10%
So in that sense, it's
a course in forgiveness.

00:56:38.700 --> 00:56:43.020 align:middle line:10%
And the goal of the course is
the attainment of inner peace.

00:56:43.020 --> 00:56:45.230 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Many people
treat it like the Bible,

00:56:45.230 --> 00:56:47.170 align:middle line:10%
like their own
version of the Bible

00:56:47.170 --> 00:56:48.376 align:middle line:10%
where they listen to quotes.

00:56:48.376 --> 00:56:49.750 align:middle line:10%
They read it over
and over again,

00:56:49.750 --> 00:56:50.960 align:middle line:10%
apply it to different areas.

00:56:50.960 --> 00:56:53.450 align:middle line:10%
And as you have throughout
the show, taken these--

00:56:53.450 --> 00:56:58.190 align:middle line:10%
I wrote one down, "A shift
in thinking from fear to love

00:56:58.190 --> 00:56:59.037 align:middle line:10%
is the miracle."

00:56:59.037 --> 00:57:01.370 align:middle line:84%
>>WILLIAMSON: Yes, the course
says a shift in perception

00:57:01.370 --> 00:57:02.870 align:middle line:90%
from fear to love.

00:57:02.870 --> 00:57:07.090 align:middle line:10%
Because since thought
is the level of cause,

00:57:07.090 --> 00:57:08.870 align:middle line:10%
if you want your life
to change, if you

00:57:08.870 --> 00:57:11.369 align:middle line:10%
want the movie to change, you
can't just go up to the screen

00:57:11.369 --> 00:57:12.820 align:middle line:10%
and try to change the plot.

00:57:12.820 --> 00:57:14.780 align:middle line:10%
What we experience out
there is the effect

00:57:14.780 --> 00:57:15.900 align:middle line:10%
of what we're thinking.

00:57:15.900 --> 00:57:19.720 align:middle line:10%
So if you want a miracle out
there, you shift your thinking.

00:57:19.720 --> 00:57:22.980 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So the
love is the cause,

00:57:22.980 --> 00:57:24.907 align:middle line:10%
and the reaction is the effect?

00:57:24.907 --> 00:57:25.740 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: Right.

00:57:25.740 --> 00:57:27.864 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you have to
shift to that place in love

00:57:27.864 --> 00:57:29.500 align:middle line:90%
for the difference to come in.

00:57:29.500 --> 00:57:31.880 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAMSON: And
love casts out fear

00:57:31.880 --> 00:57:34.260 align:middle line:10%
the same way light
casts out darkness.

00:57:34.260 --> 00:57:36.900 align:middle line:10%
You can't fight the darkness,
you just turn on the light.

00:57:36.900 --> 00:57:38.250 align:middle line:10%
You can't fight the fear.

00:57:38.250 --> 00:57:40.020 align:middle line:10%
We tend to think if
I analyze the fear,

00:57:40.020 --> 00:57:41.950 align:middle line:10%
people say how do I
move past the fear?

00:57:41.950 --> 00:57:44.210 align:middle line:10%
The only way to
move past the fear

00:57:44.210 --> 00:57:45.959 align:middle line:10%
is to move towards the love.

00:57:45.959 --> 00:57:47.000 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: Ohh, that's good.

00:57:47.000 --> 00:57:48.640 align:middle line:10%
In order to move
past the darkness,

00:57:48.640 --> 00:57:50.260 align:middle line:10%
is to move towards the light.

00:57:50.260 --> 00:57:51.593 align:middle line:90%
>>WILLIAMSON: It's the only way.

00:57:51.593 --> 00:57:53.400 align:middle line:84%
You can hit darkness
with a baseball bat.

00:57:53.400 --> 00:57:57.070 align:middle line:10%
So with career, for instance,
that you see your work

00:57:57.070 --> 00:57:58.390 align:middle line:10%
as an act of love.

00:57:58.390 --> 00:58:00.040 align:middle line:10%
It's a ministry, it's a calling.

00:58:00.040 --> 00:58:02.650 align:middle line:10%
A calling with permanent
employment given you by God

00:58:02.650 --> 00:58:03.970 align:middle line:10%
the moment you were born.

00:58:03.970 --> 00:58:07.200 align:middle line:10%
That job, can't be fired, is
to be the most loving you,

00:58:07.200 --> 00:58:09.070 align:middle line:10%
and the work that you
do-- you're an artist,

00:58:09.070 --> 00:58:10.986 align:middle line:10%
you're a salesperson,
you're a businessperson,

00:58:10.986 --> 00:58:12.030 align:middle line:10%
you're a scientist.

00:58:12.030 --> 00:58:16.210 align:middle line:84%
No, it's all just the
form, the content of which

00:58:16.210 --> 00:58:18.540 align:middle line:84%
is the love that you
are giving to the world.

00:58:18.540 --> 00:58:21.350 align:middle line:10%
People might say, well,
that sounds-- whatever.

00:58:21.350 --> 00:58:22.730 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: No, it sounds wonderful.

00:58:22.730 --> 00:58:25.240 align:middle line:84%
It sounds beautiful, and
it's Marianne Williamson.

00:58:25.240 --> 00:58:26.657 align:middle line:90%
And I just thank you so much.

00:58:26.657 --> 00:58:27.990 align:middle line:90%
>>WILLIAMSON: Thank you so much.

